qas.question: What type of "ultimate" strength is one of the two types increased the most by drying wood?
What property of wood is least affected by drying?
Is strength at elastic limit in endwise compression or stress at elastic limit in cross-bending increased more by drying wood?

answers.text: strength at elastic limit in endwise compression

qas.question: Is the strength of the modulus of rupture or elasticity increased more when wood is dried?

context: The greatest strength increase due to drying is in the ultimate <a0_0>crushing<a0_0/> strength, and <a2_0>strength at elastic limit in endwise compression<a2_0/>; these are followed by the <a3_0>modulus of rupture<a3_0/>, and stress at elastic limit in cross-bending, while the modulus of <a1_0>elasticity<a1_0/> is least affected.
